NAME
    String::Dump - Dump strings of characters for printing and debugging

SYNOPSIS
        use String::Dump <dump-hex dump-oct>;

        say 'hex: ', dump-hex($string);
        say 'oct: ', dump-oct($string);

DESCRIPTION
    When debugging or reviewing strings containing non-ASCII or non-printing
    characters, String::Dump is your friend. It provides simple functions to
    return a dump of the characters or bytes of your string in several
    different formats, such as hex, octal, decimal, and more.

